description*.en: In radiometry,"Radiant Energy} is the energy of electromagnetic waves. The quantity of radiant energy may be calculated by integrating radiant flux (or power) with respect to time.  In nuclear physics, $\textit{Radiant Energy" is energy, excluding rest energy, of the particles that are emitted, transferred, or received.
